<appendix xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" version="5.0" xml:id="app.deployment.docupdates">
  <title>Documentation Updates</title>
  <para>
  This chapter lists content changes for this document since the release of
  <phrase role="productname"><phrase os="osuse">openSUSE®</phrase><phrase os="sles">SUSE® Linux Enterprise Server</phrase><phrase os="sled">SUSE® Linux Enterprise Desktop</phrase><phrase os="slerte">SUSE® Linux Enterprise Real Time Extension</phrase></phrase> 11 SP3.
 </para>
  <para>
  This manual was updated on the following dates:
 </para>
  <!--list of xrefs, latest date sorted upmost-->
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <xref linkend="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <sect1 xml:id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga">
    <title>October 2014 (Initial Release of <phrase role="productname"><phrase os="osuse">openSUSE</phrase><phrase os="sles">SUSE Linux Enterprise Server</phrase><phrase os="sled">SUSE Linux Enterprise Desktop</phrase><phrase os="slerte">SUSE Linux Enterprise Real Time Extension</phrase></phrase> 12)</title>
    <variablelist>
      <!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
      <xi:include href="common_docupdates_general_i.xml" parse="xml"/>
      <!-- 2. Installation on AMD64 and Intel 64 -->
      <varlistentry os="sles">
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.x86"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated system requirements.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry os="sles">
        <!-- 3. Installation on IBM POWER  -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.power"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added POWER8 to the list of supported hardware (Fate#315272).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        SUSE Linux Enterprise Server 12 for POWER has moved to Little Endian. Updated affected
        parts of the documentation.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry os="sles">
        <!-- 4. Installation on IBM System z -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.zseries"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated the list of supported platforms: Removed IBM Series z9 and
        z10 machines and added IBM zEnterprise BC12.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated the memory and disk space requirements.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed instructions on how to IPL from tape—this is no longer
        supported.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Rewrote large parts of <xref linkend="sec.prep.netcfg"/> to remove
        redundant information and make it more concise.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed references to Token Ring, which is no longer supported
        (Fate#313154).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 6. Installation with YaST -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.inst"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Completely rewrote the chapter because of the new installation
        workflow.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        The installation routine now supports setting up multiple network
        devices during the installation (Fate#315680):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.network"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        The installation proposal contains a separate
        <filename>/home</filename> partition formatted with XFS (Fate#316637
        and Fate#316624):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.partitioning"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed occurrences of the YaST Repair module which has been
        dropped (Fate#308670).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Update repositories are added after having registered with SUSE Customer Center and
        can be used during installation (Fate#312012):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.addon"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Extensions and modules can be added to the system during the
        installation (Fate#316548):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.conf.manual.cc"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        SUSE Linux Enterprise Desktop can be installed as an add-on on top of SUSE Linux Enterprise Server (Fate#316436):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.addon"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem os="sles">
              <para>
        The HW crypto stack for IBM System z can be selected for
        installation via a pattern (Fate#316143):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.proposal.sofware"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Automatically importing SSH keys from a previous installation can be
        disabled (Fate#314982):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast.start.parameters.keys_users"/></para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 7. Updating SUSE Linux Enterprise -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.update.sle"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added new section: <xref linkend="sec.update.sle12"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 8. Setting Up Hardware Components with YaST -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.y2.hw"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed the following sections as the respective YaST modules are
        no longer included: <citetitle>Hardware Information</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Setting Up Graphics Card and Monitor</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Mouse Model</citetitle>, and <citetitle>Setting Up a
        Scanner</citetitle>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed content about mouse setup and adjusted
        <xref linkend="cha.y2.hw.keym"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 9. Installing or Removing Software -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.y2.sw"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Completely rewrote <xref linkend="sec.updater"/> because of changes
        in the GNOME software updater.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 10. Installing Add-On Products  -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.add-ons"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Installing add-on products or software extensions is now also
        possible without access to physical media. Added the following new
        sections: <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.register"/> and
        <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.extensions"/>. Modified
        <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.install"/> accordingly.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 16. Subscription Management -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.smt"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        For registering clients against an SMT server,
        <command>suse_register</command> has been replaced with
        <command>SUSEConnect</command> (Fate#316585).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Bugfixes</term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated chapter <xref linkend="cha.addon_creator"/> according to
        <link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=861855"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated chapter <xref linkend="cha.productcreator"/> and added
        chapter <xref linkend="cha.imgcreator"/> according to
        <link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=864033"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated section <xref linkend="sec.updater"/> according to
        <link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=839692"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed section <citetitle>Using Fingerprint
        Authentication</citetitle>. Further minor corrections and additions
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=857680"/>).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed obsolete parameter <literal>OsaMedium</literal> from
        parmfile and Cobbler examples
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=860404"/>).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Additions in section <xref linkend="sec.fb.customize"/>
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=861866"/>).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added instructions on how to add secondary languages during
        installation
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=870482"/>).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!--Installing Multiple Kernel Versions -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.tuning.multikernel"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Multiversion feature (more than one kernel installed) is enabled by
        default
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=891805"/>).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Warn about incompatible Kernel Module Packages (KPMs)
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=891805"/>).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </sect1>
</appendix>
